The paper discusses the development of a sparse solution for multi-task learning using Gaussian processes. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and social and information networks (cs.SI) as multi-task learning is a common problem in these fields.
